# Mosquitto ACL for the BoatReporter stack (used by mosquitto.conf.wan).
#
# Principle of least privilege: each boat device may only touch its own topic
# tree, and the ingest user (Telegraf) gets read-only access to everything.
#
# Usernames below must match the entries you create in the password file
# (scripts/mosquitto-passwd.sh).

# ── Telegraf ingest: read every device's telemetry/availability ────────────
user telegraf
topic read boat/#

# ── A boat device: full access to its own subtree only ─────────────────────
# Duplicate this block per device, replacing the username and MAC. The device's
# base topic is boat/<6-hex-MAC> (shown in the device's MQTT settings page).
user boat-aabbcc
topic readwrite boat/aabbcc/#

# Example second device:
# user boat-112233
# topic readwrite boat/112233/#

# ── Optional admin user: full access (for mosquitto_sub debugging) ──────────
# user admin
# topic readwrite #
